commit.message: Auto generate META.json using the plugin [MetaJSON].

Update getaddrinfo support diagnostics

getaddrinfo should work again in older Perl's with Socket 2.016.

See RT #98248: https://rt.cpan.org/Public/Bug/Display.html?id=98248

Add blank line after package

This makes sure that Dist::Zilla doesn't change line numbers when
inserting the version.

Skip db_time test on Windows

For some reason stat can return a zero mtime on Windows. Unfortunately,
I couldn't figure out why.
More conservative check for broken Socket
Disable IPv6 if it's not supported
Honor exclusions when storing private networks

Another attempt to fix Windows mtime test failures

Sleep after closing the DB file.

Use getaddrinfo instead of inet_pton

inet_pton isn't supported on some platforms.

Fix unpack_sockaddr_in for older Socket versions

Socket versions below 2.005 don't support returning an address in scalar
context.

Add dependency on Socket v1.94

This is the first Socket release that supports IPv6.

Try to fix mtime test on Windows

It looks like some Windows versions don't update mtime until the file is
closed.
